  "text": "Secondly, inspired by [CITATION_1] and [CITATION_2] , we define the laxity , nk LX (see [CITATION_3] ), which is used to describe the flexibility of the PEB charging. Note that 1) the laxity is defined for parked PEBs that wait for charging, otherwise (if the PEB is on charge or has been charged), the laxity is invalid; 2) for a new time interval, laxity values should be updated; 3) for a given k , a specific n i can be found if PEB end for Armed with PEB C got by Algorithm 1, we are then able to skip auxiliary variables , nk u and , nk v and seek for the ESS charging and discharging strategy through Model C. Note that, in the heuristics-based method, the control strategies of PEBs and ESS are generated separately and the PEB coordinated charging is dispatched heuristically so that the final strategy is not necessarily the optimal strategy.",
